Giles of Rome OESA, Commentary on Aristotle, De anima

description: CCCC MS 234 contains two work by Giles of Rome OESA (c. 1243-1316), the Commentary on Aristotle's De generatione et corruptione and an incomplete version of the Commentary on Aristotle's De anima. The manuscript is written throughout in a cursive, heavily abbreviated fifteenth-century hand and nothing is known of how it came to be in Parker's collection.
